Former chairman of the Pension Reform Taskforce Team, Abdulrasheed Maina, has been released from the Kuje prison in Abuja.
Maina, his son and company are standing trial over allegation of money laundering charges. His lawyer, Ademola Adedipe, from the chamber of Ahmed Raji, (SAN), confirmed his release after over six months in detention.
Adedioe said Maina was released on Monday night after all the conditions for his release were met. He also said apart from the conditions set for his release, administrative bottleneck was also part of the delay for his release months after he was granted bail.